args: If someone told you about a mysterious\nworld that could make your every dream\ncome true, wouldn't you want to go?
Well, THAT was awful. I didn't get enough\nalone time with my darling at all.
And by ＂not enough,＂ I mean I didn't get\nONE SINGLE MOMENT ALONE WITH HIM\nat the Halloween party!
Why does everyone have to love him so\nmuch?! Every other moment, someone\nwas coming by to talk to him!
Ah, well. I suppose I'll just have to hide\nin the fireplace and surprise him later.
You there! I don't care if you're a thief\nor a fiend—I'm in a VERY bad mood,\nand you are going to pay!
Where IS this blasted thing? In here?\n...Wait. I don't remember a room ever\nbeing here before.
Hey! I'm not a fiend! I'm the Halloween...\nOh, never mind.
Here. By way of apology for the scare,\nyou can have this outfit.
Now THIS is my kind of getup. My darling's\neyes are going to turn into little jackpots\nwhen they behold me in this!
Your every dream is going to come true.
Huh? What? Wait, say that last part again!
This is more than a costume—it lets you\nbecome a whole new person.
Isn't that the entire point of a costume?
Yes, but other costumes only allow you\nto pretend. This one makes it REAL.
Like, let's say you're a dragon who's\nhopelessly in love with a human.\nJust as an example.
H-how do you know about that?!
Regardless, wouldn't you like to try living\na different life with this human?
Right now, he's a wandering prince.\nBut what if he were a merchant?\nOr an artist?
You might be enjoying an entirely\ndifferent sort of life together!
You mean this outfit will allow me to\nexperience any number of different\nlives with my darling?
Perhaps even a life where I was born\nhuman and we were happily married?
Sure, whatever you want! Just throw that\nbaby on, and the world's your oyster.
And a happy Halloween to you too, spirit!
What even WAS that strange creature...?\nNo. No time for that now. I must focus\nfirst and foremost on this costume.
I thought it was just a fancy costume for\nHalloween, but it is SO MUCH MORE!\nI must don it right away!
Right then! Off to Mym's fantasy land!
But which life should I choose first...?\nAh! I know!

What if the two of us were happily married
and living in a house far from meddlers
who seek to steal my darling's time like
common time burglars?
We'd be lovey-dovey until the cows\ncome home! It's PERFECT!
...Goodness, look at this little cottage!\nIs this our new love nest?
Er, did you forget your own house, Mym?
Darling! Um, this may sound a bit silly,\nbut you and I are...married, yes?
Of course! You are my one and only wife,\nand that will never change.
We've forged lives together through thick\nand thin in this poor and wretched land.\nDo you really not remember that?
(I did it! He is mine, and mine alone!)
(My every dream has finally come true!)
Are you sure you're all right? It's not like\nyou to ask such an obvious question.
I guess I'm just not fully awake yet.
Now, let's get out there and spend some\nquality time in the vegetable garden!
We live in the middle of nowhere, darling.\nWe must grow food if we're to survive.
(Hrrm. Well, this WAS what I wished for,\nbut it's not quite what I was expecting.)
(This imaginary world might be a tad\nmore work than I first anticipated.)
Let's split up and plow the fields, my love.\nCan you handle that bit over there?
(Ugh. I've barely moved and I'm already\ntired. How DO these humans stand living\nin such weak flesh sacks?)
(I'm experiencing the same hardships\nhe is... Oh, this is all so NEW!)
(This must be what it truly means\nto be a married couple!)
Thus did the two of them live happily ever after\nas husband and wife. Or so she thought...
It's night, darling! Come to bed!
Just a little longer, my sweet.\nThese weeds are endless!
There we go. Grow big and strong now,\nyou little onions and carrots!
Ugh! Why won't he pay attention to me?!
I thought I'd be the center of his world if\nwe removed people from it, but now his\nattention has been hijacked by produce!
Oh no! Those bugs are eating my cabbage!
Surely it can wait until tomorrow, darling?\nThe moon is already quite high in the sky.
I can't turn my back on suffering\nvegetables, Mym!
We're the only ones who can save them!
*sigh* It seems he can't help but rush in\nwhenever anything is suffering.
I realize he's like that in the real world,\nbut I didn't know it would carry over here.
We're a married couple now!\nHe should love me above all others—\nINCLUDING root veggies!
How am I ever going to create the perfect\nworld where we are together?
Should I wish for a world where he won't\nsave people OR vegetables? Hmm, but\nif I do that, he's not really him...
Oh, of COURSE! I just need to wish for\na world where nothing ever suffers!
Right! I'll dream up a world where the\nShard is still intact and the country is\nat complete peace! It's perfect!
In my next world, my darling will rule\nover a land where no one wants for even\nthe slightest of things!
And I will be his princess!
